## ğŸ”„ 7. Git & Collaboration Flow

### ğŸª´ Branch Structure

| Branch      | Purpose                                     |
| ----------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `main`      | Stable, demo-ready version                  |
| `develop`   | Active development branch                   |
| `feature/*` | Feature work (e.g., `feature/deposit-form`) |
| `fix/*`     | Bug fixes                                   |
| `chore/*`   | Setup, config, documentation                |

### ğŸ§­ Workflow

```bash
# Pull latest
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop

# Create new feature
git checkout -b feature/deposit-form

# Commit work
git add .
git commit -m "feat(deposit): add DepositPage and DepositForm"

# Push branch
git push -u origin feature/deposit-form
```

Open a **Pull Request** to `develop`.
After review â†’ merge â†’ deploy to demo.
At milestone â†’ merge `develop` â†’ `main`.

### ğŸ§¾ Commit Convention

| Type        | Meaning            |
| ----------- | ------------------ |
| `feat:`     | New feature        |
| `fix:`      | Bug fix            |
| `refactor:` | Code restructuring |
| `docs:`     | Documentation      |
| `chore:`    | Config, cleanup    |

---

## âœ… 8. Completion Checklist

Before merging a feature PR:

* [ ] Code passes ESLint & Prettier checks.
* [ ] Component split follows **Containerâ€“Presentation** pattern.
* [ ] API calls handled via **TanStack Query**.
* [ ] State handled via **Zustand**.
* [ ] UI tested in both **light/dark** modes.
* [ ] Toast notifications shown on all actions.
* [ ] Screenshots attached to PR.
* [ ] Reviewed and approved by 1 teammate.

